Press Releases.Title: No New Cases of Locally Transmitted  Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 15 February 2021, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed that there are no new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. 

There are 9 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.

We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

 

 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
15 FEBRUARY 2021
